                <p rend="flushleft">I. <hi rend="italic">Italian Reparations</hi>.</p>
                <p>The Council considered the Report submitted by the Reparation Committee. It was
                        <hi rend="italic">noted</hi> that no agreement had been reached on this
                    subject.</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">II. <hi rend="italic">Questions Still Outstanding</hi>.</p>
                <p>1. <hi rend="italic">Tenda and Briga</hi>.</p>
                <p>M. Bidault said that the Commission of Enquiry for Tenda and Briga had returned
                    to Paris and that the Council would be able to examine their Report as soon as
                    it was tabled.</p>
                <p>2. <hi rend="italic">Germany</hi>.</p>
                <p>M. Bidault reminded the Council that its Agenda also called for a study of the
                    German problem.</p>
                <p>3. <hi rend="italic">Draft Treaty with Finland</hi>.</p>
                <p>Mr. Bevin asked whether the 1921 and 1940 Conventions concerning the Aaland
                    Islands should be mentioned in the Peace Treaty and suggested referring this
                    question to the Deputies for consideration. The Council <hi rend="italic"
                        >agreed</hi>.</p>
                <pb facs="0329" n="309" xml:id="pg_309"/>
                <p rend="flushleft">III. <hi rend="italic">Future Procedure of the Council of
                        Foreign Ministers</hi>.</p>
                <p>The U.S. Delegation proposed that: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>The Deputies should submit to the Council a Report indicating which
                            points in the five Peace Treaties were agreed and which were still under
                            discussion.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>Such Report to be submitted to the Peace Conference, which might be
                            convened for 15th June.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>The Council <hi rend="italic">adopted</hi> the first part of the U.S. proposal
                    and reserved its decision on the second.</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">IV. <hi rend="italic">Next Meeting of the Council</hi>.</p>
                <p>The Council <hi rend="italic">agreed</hi> to hold its next meeting on 9th May at
                    5 p.m. to consider the Report of the Deputies referred to above.</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">V. <hi rend="italic">Next Meeting of Deputies</hi>.</p>
                <p>It was <hi rend="italic">agreed</hi> that the Deputies should meet that day in
                    the afternoon to prepare the Report asked for by the Council.</p>
